//
// In C these are enum values.  In Rust we use i32 constants for Phase A
// (faithful to `Token.token: int` in C) with a TODO for a proper enum in Phase B.
//
// C: enum RESERVED { TK_AND = FIRST_RESERVED, TK_BREAK, ... }

